The contributor guide is no longer a single hand-edited file. It is built from `agents-md/sections/` fragments, exposed through `lib.agentsMd.{sections, profiles, targets, documents, render}`, and rendered by `nix run .#agents-md`. A flake check enforces that the committed `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md` match the generated output.

```nix
lib.agentsMd.render {
  target = "codex";
  enabledSections =
    lib.agentsMd.profiles.nix
    ++ [ "imageConventions" ];
  extraSectionsByTarget.codex = [
    "## Codex-only notes\n\nPut Codex-specific guidance here."
  ];
}
```

Sibling repos can pull in shared guidance instead of copy-pasting it. The default command shows the checkout diff, using `delta` for interactive terminals and plain unified diff text for pipes and logs.

```bash
nix run .#agents-md              # shows checkout diff
nix run .#agents-md -- --write   # writes AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md
nix run .#agents-md -- --check
```
